alert_notes.note:
Clearly, to get the gist of my conversation, you need to hear it. Forwarded from Jen At approx 4:20 PM.
The customer started going on and on about how he was not informed of the contract or the cost, his interest rate being wrong, his insurer was wrongly noted as he is with Desjardins not Allstate. After listening very patiently, I asked him to please tell me what I can do for him. I believe he wanted me to refund the warranty along with all interest paid on his price of the warranty. I told him I could not do that and perhaps he'd be better of contacting Carleton Place Ford or Scotia Bank. He told me that Terry, the general manager of Carleton Place Ford will be contacting CGW to have the whole warranty reversed. He also told me that the consumer protecting act clearly states that if the seller doesn't clearly tell the buyer about the warranty, it's illegal to charge for it. I explained that we could not take responsibility for what anyone at Carleton Place said or did not say.
I honestly believe the customer was under the influence.  A.H.
